ExecDesc.value: D-Link HNAP Request Stack Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A remote code execution vulnerability exists in D-Link routers. The vulnerability is due to a stack buffer overflow while processing crafted HTTP POST requests addressed to the HNAP handler. By sending a crafted HTTP request to the target device, a remote unauthenticated attacker can exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the affected device with root privileges.
